):979-980. [<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/entrez/query.fcgi?cmd=Retrieve&amp;db=PubMed&amp;list_uids=10551195&amp;dopt=Abstract" target="_blank">Medline</a>]</span></li><li><span id="ref21">Garfield E. How can impact factors be improved? BMJ.  Aug 17, 1996;313(7054):411-413. [<a target="_blank" href="https://dx.doi.org/10.1136/bmj.313.7054.411">CrossRef</a>] [<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/entrez/query.fcgi?cmd=Retrieve&amp;db=PubMed&amp;list_uids=8761234&amp;dopt=Abstract" target="_blank">Medline</a>]</span></li><li><span id="ref22">Pagni M, Khan NR, Cohen HL, Choudhri AF. Highly cited works in radiology: the top 100 cited articles in radiologic journals. Acad Radiol.  Aug 2014;21(8):1056-1066. [<a target="_blank" href="https://dx.doi.org/10.1016/j.acra.2014.03.011">CrossRef</a>] [<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/entrez/query.fcgi?cmd=Retrieve&amp;db=PubMed&amp;list_uids=24833569&amp;dopt=Abstract" target="_blank">Medline</a>]</span></li><li><span id="ref23">Brandt JS, Hadaya O, Schuster M, Rosen T, Sauer MV, Ananth CV. A bibliometric analysis of top-cited journal articles in obstetrics and gynecology. JAMA Netw Open.  Dec 2, 2019;2(12):e1918007. [<a target="_blank" href="https://dx.doi.org/10.1001/jamanetworkopen.2019.18007">CrossRef</a>] [<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/entrez/query.fcgi?cmd=Retrieve&amp;db=PubMed&amp;list_uids=31860106&amp;dopt=Abstract" target="_blank">Medline</a>]</span></li><li><span id="ref24">Li T, Kang C, Ren G,  et al. Top 100 cited articles related to EUS: A bibliometric analysis. Endosc Ultrasound.   2024;13(4):259-268. [<a target="_blank" href="https://dx.doi.org/10.1097/eus.0000000000000081">CrossRef</a>] [<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/entrez/query.fcgi?cmd=Retrieve&amp;db=PubMed&amp;list_uids=39318756&amp;dopt=Abstract" target="_blank">Medline</a>]</span></li><li><span id="ref25">Moher D, Liberati A, Tetzlaff J, Altman DG, The PRISMA Group. Preferred Reporting Items for Systematic Reviews and Meta-An