0059-z">CrossRef</a>]</span></li><li><span id="ref45">Ogden TL, Bartley DL. The ups and downs of journal impact factors. Ann Occup Hyg.  Mar 2008;52(2):73-82. [<a target="_blank" href="https://dx.doi.org/10.1093/annhyg/men002">CrossRef</a>] [<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/entrez/query.fcgi?cmd=Retrieve&amp;db=PubMed&amp;list_uids=18316351&amp;dopt=Abstract" target="_blank">Medline</a>]</span></li><li><span id="ref46">Mishra S, Fegley BD, Diesner J, Torvik VI. Self-citation is the hallmark of productive authors, of any gender. PLoS ONE.   2018;13(9):e0195773. [<a target="_blank" href="https://dx.doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0195773">CrossRef</a>] [<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/entrez/query.fcgi?cmd=Retrieve&amp;db=PubMed&amp;list_uids=30256792&amp;dopt=Abstract" target="_blank">Medline</a>]</span></li></ol></div><br><hr><a name="Abbreviations">&#x200E;</a><h4 class="navigation-heading" id="Abbreviations" data-label="Abbreviations">Abbreviations</h4><table width="80%" border="0" align="center"><tr><td><b>AsPEN:</b> Asian Pharmacoepidemiology Network</td></tr><tr><td><b>CDM:</b> Common Data Model</td></tr><tr><td><b>EHR:</b> electronic health record</td></tr><tr><td><b>OMOP:</b> Observational Medical Outcomes Partnership</td></tr><tr><td><b>PRISMA:</b> Preferred Reporting Items for Systematic Reviews and Meta-Analyses</td></tr><tr><td><b>TCpY:</b> Total Citations per Year</td></tr><tr><td><b>VSD:</b> Vaccine Safety Datalink</td></tr><tr><td><b>WoSCC:</b> Web of Science Core Collection</td></tr></table><br><hr><p style="font-style: italic">Edited by  Andrew Coristine; submitted 05.02.25; peer-reviewed by Ali Jafarizadeh,  Xiongfeng Huang; final revised version received 06.05.25; accepted 20.05.25; published 28.07.25.</p><a href="https://support.jmir.org/hc/en-us/articles/115002955531" id="Copyright" target="_blank" class="navigation-heading h4 d-block" aria-label="Copyright - what is a Creative Commons License?" data-label="Copyright">Copyright <span clas